⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Baby Metroid (the Hatchling)
node MET · MET · ⟦The Baby Metroid (the Hatchling):MET:ba2aed⟧

WHO   — The Baby Metroid (the Hatchling) — the hatchling
WHAT  — The infant creature at the broken heart of Super Metroid — kidnapped, weaponized, and made vast by the Pirates, who returns at the climax to know its mother, shield her, and give everything it has so that she may live.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because it knew Samus first; because the bond made when it hatched outlasts captivity and corruption; because even a thing bred to drain life can choose, once, to give it away.
HOW   — By the life-draining touch that defines its kind — turned, at the end, from theft to gift — pouring its own energy into Samus to pull her back from death before Mother Brain, then dying empty so she does not.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was hatched to its mother and stolen to its enemy — and in the last room I remembered which one I loved.

spoken token : lim-braen-deix   ·   hex : ba2aed
